<plot>Frankie Laine and his wife, Nan Grey, open up an antique store in Hollywood, and many film actors drop by to wish them success. Among the droppers-by, all working in or appearing in recent films produced by Columbia Pictures, are John Derek, Joanne Dru, Smiley Burnette, Jock O'Mahoney, John Ireland and Ruth Warrick. Frankie Laine does not sing in this short, but he does sing a lot in the Columbia film this short was made for to plug, "Rainbow 'Round My Shoulder."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?482175</url></doc>
